nts1.n: TEARS IN THE CLUB W/ JEUNE POUCE
nts1.d: "Tears in the Club" presents a unique blend of structured and chaotic music, combining intense hip hop, drum and bass, footwork, jersey club, and sometimes Afro rhythms. This multi-genre musical show explores diverse musical landscapes, creating a striking contrast between genres, while also showcasing new artists.

Artist and selector Fatima drops by NTS London studio once a month to play her favourite tunes. A laid back waffle infused show draped in the finest of audible garments, presenting some the worlds hardest ear candy.
contemporary french + international rap presented by Stephane.
What do you get when you mix 1990s Memphis Rap with elements of jazz and funk?

Ruf Dug brings the leftfield: old video game soundtracks, dusty analogue dreamers and poolside Balearic sounds. No nonsense from the original tropical cyberpunk.
From the host: "Das Druid - Freedom - OUT NOW!!! This week's show is built around the remixes myself and Justin Robertson did of this killer Aussie baggy band…"
Ira demonstrates how to do extra soulful with a masterclass in vibes. It's easy when you know how.

In an era of everything at once, Gabrielle Kwarteng is a DJ who weaves stories that often look to the past, while always focusing on possible futures. Dip in to hear a range of dance music from downtempo to deep house to techno rollers - and everything in between.
Celebrating 20 years, Innervisions brings its sound to NTS with monthly shows featuring its core artists and special guests.

ENDLESS rolls through NTS on a monthly basis. Sounding like Empyrean cracked open, the airwaves morph into into a tunnel linking South London to the end of the world through blown-out drums & and redlined ambience. Including exclusive dubs and guest mixes from friends.

nts2.d: Visual artist and ceramicist Aaron Angell plays a vinyl-only monthly selection of music from his collection - usually focussing on guitar soli, privately pressed UK folk, psychedelia, and the occult new age.

Takashi Yoshimatsu, born in Tokyo in 1953, is one of Japan's most renowned living classical composers. First gaining recognition in the early 1980s with atonal, serialist compositions like "Threnody to Toki" (1981). Yoshimatsu later became disillusioned with atonal music, opting to compose lush neo-romantic sounds taking influence from popular rock and jazz. Yoshimatsu also notably composed the soundtrack for the 2003 film adaption of Astro Boy.
Image: Naoki Hashimoto
Amsterdam selector Orpheu The Wizard connects oddball and straight forward jams from different decades and different record shelves in a monthly show.

Monthly sessions from Zaltan, the mind behind Paris-based leftfield dance, electronic & downtempo imprint Antinote, with occasional appearances from friends and artists on the label.
From the host: "Antinote welcomes After bobby Williams, the IDM / experimental duo from Berlin. Following their first E.P. on Antinote in 2025 ABW offers an hour of unreleased original music and recent descovery. A second E.P. will come in March."
Amman-based club producer and DJ Toumba selects two hours of sounds influenced by the bedouin musical tradition and beyond.
A monthly broadcasts from London-based curator Cynthia, taking you through a selection of her ongoing music research and personal favourites, blending sounds that move across time and genre.
Brussels-based composer Christina Vantzou whose music explores “time expansion, atmospheres, harmonies, and the affects that arise from them” shares an hour of selections.
Tracing the common influences between new collaborators drone rock pioneers and Detroit rap producer and DJ Black Noi$e.

A monthly transmission of displaced rock n roll, exotic punk and early electronics, paying favor to all things primitive and sleazy. LA visual artist Amanda Siegel delves into the international underground, offering a thorough sonic survey of protopunk, hard rock, synthpunk, powerpop, psych, industrial and more.

nts2.n: ALL ABOUT OUR LOVE W/ HARRIET BROWN
nts2.d:
Sit down, cool off and unwind with Harriet Brown's soothing monthly showcase, live from our LA studio.
From the host: "An episode for the new year – for reflecting on the past, for cradling warmth and light despite the cold, dark state of the world. Music for holding yourself, holding your loved ones, holding on to hope for rebirth

Enter a world of mahjong, star-crossed lovers, and cigarette smoke. Tune in for sounds of the past and the present across the Asian diaspora.
From the host: _"Welcome to Angie’s Club. A sweaty dance mix gathered from underground scenes across Asia. Dance to an hour of footwork, club, house, techno, and everything in between." _

subtle.d: Sessions w/ Amy B is an underground multi-genre music show, showcasing the most prolific guests from all corners of the music industry.

Originally linking up in Wellington and playing shows with the Breaking Beats crew, Swampman and Zero Crumbs have reunited – bringing their smooth mixing and flexible selections to East London. 

In their monthly show, the pair explore the deep, dark, and soulful ends of DNB. Expect fresh underground tunes, deep cut classics, and a bit of banter in Kiwi accents.

subtle.n: Dun Roamin w/ Tomi From Brockley

subtle.d:
Midlands born, London based producer and DJ influenced by UK funky, broken techno, garage and early dubstep. 

Has released on Keysound recordings, RKS, eatmybeat, ec2a, Durkle Disco and Dimsum records

2Step Selects is a monthly show hosted by the Choki Biki Records crew. Founded in Dublin, Ireland, CBR consists of DJ Sharpson, 2step.png, Frame Shift, and MICK. The show consists of an all round breaks, electro, ukg and jungle hour, followed by an Irish showcase, demonstrating all the best Ireland has to offer collective/party/Dj & Producer wise!

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

subtle.n: The Ice Box Sessions with Frigid

subtle.d: Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".
